urls.title: Liquidation
urls.description: When the Health Factor of a position is below one. the position becomes subject to liquidation.

data.text:
ParaSpace is also introducing a new liquidation model to support this cross-margin framework:
• ERC-20 liquidates before ERC-721
• Liquidator is capped and can only liquidate until HF is 1.5

ParaSpace’s liquidator can only improve a portfolio’s HF.
https://t.co/eDtTiL1bSR

ParaSpace Cross-Margin Model ex:

Purchase 3 BAYCs w/ 5 BAYCs + 50k USDC as collateral.

1. Supply 5 BAYC + 50k USDC
2. Borrow 200 ETH
3. Purchase 3 BAYCs

If the health factor of the portfolio approaches 1, top off portfolio w/ ERC-721 and/or ERC-20 assets to avoid liquidation. https://t.co/8AaVMiaSBo

With a cross-margin model, users can collateralize assets into 1 portfolio and borrow against the portfolio’s total value.

Plus, with ParaSpace users can collateralize both ERC-721 & ERC-20 assets into 1 portfolio giving flexibility and freedom to truly manage risk and exposure. https://t.co/qezDvRpU7t

Isolated-Margin Model ex:

Purchase 3 BAYCs w/ 10 BAYCs as collateral

1. Supply 1 BAYC for 20 ETH
2. Repeat Step 1 x9
3. Purchase 3 BAYCs w/ 200 ETH from all open positions

If the health factor of ANY position approaches 1, the loan must be immediately paid to avoid liquidation https://t.co/K6beKEOdoX

Traditional NFT lending follows an isolated-margin model and requires users to take out individual positions against each NFT.

While this model allows users to manage risk per position, as the # of positions increases, so does the management required to avoid liquidation. https://t.co/ehZctzrFmS
